---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const steps = [
  {
    title: 'The starting point',
    content: `I wanted a professional portfolio website but didn't want to spend weeks learning web development from scratch or pay a developer for something I'd need to update myself constantly. I decided to try building it with Claude Code — Anthropic's AI coding assistant — to see how far I could get as a non-engineer.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'Choosing the stack',
    content: `Claude recommended Astro + Tailwind CSS. Astro is a modern static site generator that produces fast, SEO-friendly pages and requires minimal JavaScript. Tailwind CSS is a utility-first styling framework that makes it easy to build responsive designs without writing custom CSS. Neither requires a backend or database — just files.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'The build process',
    content: `I described what I wanted in plain language: a portfolio for a Senior PM in Jakarta, 6 pages, dark navy design, mobile responsive. Claude initialized the project, configured Tailwind, created a shared layout with navigation, and built all six pages in a single session. I reviewed each page, gave feedback, and Claude iterated.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'What surprised me',
    content: `The speed. Going from a blank folder to a working, styled, multi-page site took hours, not weeks. Claude handled the technical details — file structure, Astro component syntax, Tailwind configuration, mobile responsiveness — while I focused on the content and direction. That's a great division of labour.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'What I still had to do',
    content: `Replace all the placeholder content with real case studies, add my actual photo, customize colors and copy to match my voice, set up a domain and hosting (I used [your hosting provider]). The AI built the structure; I filled it with substance.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'What I learned',
    content: `As a PM, this experience reinforced something I already believed: you don't need to know how to code to work effectively with engineers. Understanding what's possible, asking the right questions, and being specific about outcomes matters more than knowing the syntax. Claude Code is a great tool for PMs who want to prototype or build lightweight tools without a full engineering team.`,
  },
];
---

<Layout title="How I Built This" description="Behind the scenes: building this PM portfolio with Claude Code and Astro.">

  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="relative py-24 overflow-hidden border-b border-white/10">
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-1/4 w-96 h-96 bg-sky-500/10 rounded-full filter blur-[120px] -z-10 animate-pulse"></div>
    
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 relative">
      <p class="text-sky-400 font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-sky-400 animate-pulse"></span>
        Technical Literacy & AI
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-6xl font-extrabold mb-6 bg-clip-text text-transparent bg-gradient-to-r from-white via-slate-200 to-sky-400">
        How I Built This
      </h1>
      <p class="text-slate-300 text-lg max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        A transparent walkthrough of how a non-engineer PM built this portfolio site using
        Claude Code, Astro, and Tailwind CSS — in a single session.
      </p>

      <!-- Tech badges -->
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-8">
        {['Claude Code', 'Astro 5', 'Tailwind CSS v4', 'Node.js'].map(tech => (
          <span class="px-3 py-1.5 border border-white/20 text-slate-300 text-sm rounded-lg">{tech}</span>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick summary -->
  <section class="py-16 border-b border-white/10">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {[
          { label: 'Time to build', value: '~1 session', desc: 'From blank folder to working site' },
          { label: 'Lines of code written by me', value: '~0', desc: 'Claude handled all the code' },
          { label: 'Pages', value: '6', desc: 'Home, About, Case Studies, Services, This page, Contact' },
        ].map(stat => (
          <div class="group border border-white/10 rounded-2xl p-6 bg-white/[0.03] backdrop-blur-md hover:bg-white/[0.07] hover:border-sky-400/50 transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1">
            <p class="text-slate-500 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-3">{stat.label}</p>
            <p class="text-4xl font-black text-white group-hover:text-sky-400 transition-colors mb-2 drop-shadow-[0_0_10px_rgba(56,189,248,0.3)]">{stat.value}</p>
            <p class="text-slate-400 text-xs leading-relaxed">{stat.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Story steps -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="space-y-12">
        {steps.map((step, i) => (
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto,1fr] gap-6">
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-sky-500/10 border border-sky-400/30 flex items-center justify-center text-sky-400 text-sm font-black flex-shrink-0 shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(56,189,248,0.2)]">
                {i + 1}
              </div>
              {i < steps.length - 1 && (
                <div class="w-px flex-1 bg-white/10 mt-3"></div>
              )}
            </div>
            <div class="pb-4">
              <h2 class="text-white font-bold text-xl mb-3">{step.title}</h2>
              <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">{step.content}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PM takeaway -->
  <section class="py-16 border-t border-white/10">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="relative group p-8 lg:p-12 rounded-[2rem] border border-white/10 bg-gradient-to-b from-white/5 to-transparent backdrop-blur-sm overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute -top-24 -right-24 w-48 h-48 bg-sky-500/10 rounded-full blur-[80px]"></div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">The PM perspective</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
          Building this taught me that AI-assisted development changes the build/buy/borrow calculus for PMs.
          Things that previously required a developer (a portfolio site, a simple internal tool, a prototype)
          are now within reach for someone who can articulate requirements clearly and iterate quickly.
          That's a product skill. The bar isn't "can you code" — it's "can you think clearly about what you want."
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Want to do the same? -->
  <section class="py-16 border-t border-white/10">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Want to build yours?</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-8 max-w-lg mx-auto">
        I help other PMs build their portfolio and present their work effectively.
        Check out my services or reach out directly.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/services" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 bg-sky-500 hover:bg-sky-400 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg transition-colors">
          View Services
        </a>
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 border border-sky-400/40 text-sky-400 hover:bg-sky-400/10 font-semibold rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Get in Touch
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
